&ldquo;If it walks like a duck, and it quacks like a duck, then it must be a duck.&rdquo;
Dynamic typing(Duck typing in particular) is one of the main reasons why python is so popular today. The learning curve for python much lower than static-typed languages like C and Java, because there is less &ldquo;boiler-plate&rdquo; involved in writing code.
Having experienced both static and dynamic typed languages, I have come to appreciate the assurances provided by static typed languages, which has improved my development experience.
